---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const html = `<style>
    body { background: var(--innovia-navy); color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78); }
    .site-header { background: rgba(15,36,71,0.94); backdrop-filter: blur(12px); border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.10); }
    .site-header nav > a { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); }
    .site-header nav > a:hover, .site-header nav > a.active { color: #fff; }
    .site-header .btn-navy { background: #fff; color: var(--innovia-navy); }
    .site-header .btn-navy:hover { background: var(--innovia-green); color: var(--innovia-navy); }

    .page-hero { padding: 56px 0 56px; position: relative; overflow: hidden; }
    .page-hero::after { content: ""; position: absolute; inset: 0; background: radial-gradient(circle at 92% 8%, rgba(149,208,49,0.14) 0%, transparent 38%), radial-gradient(circle at 4% 96%, rgba(42,74,120,0.5) 0%, transparent 50%); pointer-events: none; }
    .page-hero .container { position: relative; z-index: 1; }
    .page-hero .crumb { display: flex; gap: 10px; align-items: center; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); letter-spacing: 0.04em; padding-bottom: 14px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.18); margin-bottom: 36px; }
    .page-hero .crumb a:hover { color: #fff; }
    .page-hero h1 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 900; font-size: clamp(48px, 6vw, 88px); letter-spacing: -0.034em; color: #fff; line-height: 1; margin: 0; text-wrap: balance; }
    .page-hero h1 em { color: var(--innovia-green); font-style: normal; }
    .page-hero h1 .light { display: block; margin-top: 8px; font-family: var(--font-body); font-weight: 300; font-style: italic; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55); font-size: 0.48em; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
    .page-hero .lede { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.62; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78); max-width: 56ch; margin: 24px 0 0; }
    
  
    .pillar-detail { padding: 24px 0 96px; }
    .pillar-detail .layout { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.5fr; gap: 64px; align-items: start; }
    .pillar-detail .col-left { position: sticky; top: 96px; }
    .pillar-detail .num { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 900; font-size: 112px; letter-spacing: -0.04em; color: var(--innovia-green); line-height: 0.85; margin: 0; }
    .pillar-detail .legacy { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55); letter-spacing: 0.06em; padding-top: 16px; margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.18); }
    .pillar-detail .legacy s { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.32); }
    .pillar-detail .col-right { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.18); border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.18); }
    .pillar-detail .facet { padding: 32px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12); display: grid; grid-template-columns: 56px 1fr; gap: 24px; align-items: start; }
    .pillar-detail .facet:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
    .pillar-detail .facet .ix { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--innovia-green); letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; padding-top: 6px; }
    .pillar-detail .facet h4 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: 22px; color: #fff; letter-spacing: -0.012em; margin: 0 0 8px; }
    .pillar-detail .facet p { font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.72); margin: 0; max-width: 56ch; }

    .related { padding: 80px 0 96px; background: var(--innovia-navy-deep); border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); }
    .related .ix { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--innovia-green); letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; }
    .related h2 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: clamp(28px, 3vw, 40px); color: #fff; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin: 14px 0 32px; }
    .related .grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 16px; }
    .related a { padding: 24px 26px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12); display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; text-decoration: none; color: inherit; transition: border-color .15s, background .15s; }
    .related a:hover { border-color: var(--innovia-green); background: rgba(149,208,49,0.06); }
    .related a .ix { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); font-size: 10px; }
    .related a h3 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: 19px; color: #fff; letter-spacing: -0.008em; margin: 0; }
    .related a .arrow { margin-top: auto; padding-top: 12px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.10); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--innovia-green); letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; }
    @media (max-width: 1080px) { .pillar-detail .layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 32px; } .pillar-detail .col-left { position: static; } .related .grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

    /* === Deep-dive narrative sections === */
    .tp-pressure { padding: 88px 0; background: var(--innovia-navy-deep); border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); }
    .tp-pressure .layout { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.6fr; gap: 72px; align-items: start; }
    .tp-pressure .ix { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--innovia-green); letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; }
    .tp-pressure h2 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 800; font-size: clamp(30px, 3.4vw, 46px); color: #fff; letter-spacing: -0.022em; line-height: 1.05; margin: 14px 0 0; text-wrap: balance; }
    .tp-pressure .body p { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.65; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78); margin: 0 0 18px; max-width: 60ch; }
    .tp-pressure .body p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
    .tp-pressure .pull { font-family: var(--font-display); font-style: italic; font-weight: 500; font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.4; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6); border-left: 2px solid var(--innovia-green); padding: 6px 0 6px 18px; margin: 28px 0 0; max-width: 52ch; }
    .tp-pressure .pull cite { display: block; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-family: var(--font-mono); letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.42); margin-top: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; }

    .tp-mechanic { padding: 88px 0; }
    .tp-mechanic .head { max-width: 56ch; margin-bottom: 48px; }
    .tp-mechanic .ix { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--innovia-green); letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; }
    .tp-mechanic h2 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 800; font-size: clamp(28px, 3vw, 42px); color: #fff; letter-spacing: -0.02em; line-height: 1.05; margin: 14px 0 0; text-wrap: balance; }
    .tp-mechanic .steps { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 0; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.18); border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.18); }
    .tp-mechanic .step { padding: 28px 24px 32px 0; border-right: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12); }
    .tp-mechanic .step:last-child { border-right: 0; padding-right: 0; }
    .tp-mechanic .step + .step { padding-left: 28px; }
    .tp-mechanic .step .ix { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--innovia-green); letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; }
    .tp-mechanic .step h4 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: 20px; color: #fff; letter-spacing: -0.012em; margin: 12px 0 8px; }
    .tp-mechanic .step p { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.58; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin: 0; }

    .tp-proof { padding: 64px 0; background: var(--innovia-navy-deep); border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); }
    .tp-proof .strip { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 0; align-items: start; }
    .tp-proof .stat { padding: 0 32px; border-right: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12); }
    .tp-proof .stat:first-child { padding-left: 0; }
    .tp-proof .stat:last-child { padding-right: 0; border-right: 0; }
    .tp-proof .stat .num { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 800; font-size: clamp(36px, 4.2vw, 56px); color: #fff; letter-spacing: -0.024em; line-height: 1; display: block; }
    .tp-proof .stat .num.placeholder { background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(149,208,49,0.18) 0%, rgba(149,208,49,0.06) 100%); padding: 4px 10px; border-radius: 4px; }
    .tp-proof .stat .label { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-top: 14px; display: block; line-height: 1.4; }

    .tp-deep { padding: 96px 0; }
    .tp-deep .head { margin-bottom: 36px; max-width: 60ch; }
    .tp-deep .ix { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--innovia-green); letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; }
    .tp-deep h2 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 800; font-size: clamp(30px, 3.4vw, 46px); color: #fff; letter-spacing: -0.022em; line-height: 1.05; margin: 14px 0 0; text-wrap: balance; }
    .tp-deep .body { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 56px; max-width: 100%; }
    .tp-deep .body p { font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.65; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78); margin: 0 0 18px; }
    .tp-deep .body p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
    .tp-deep .body p strong { color: #fff; font-weight: 600; }
    .tp-deep .subhead { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: 22px; color: #fff; letter-spacing: -0.012em; margin: 0 0 14px; }
    .tp-deep .panel { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.10); padding: 28px; margin-top: 40px; }
    .tp-deep .panel .ix-small { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; color: var(--innovia-green); letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; }
    .tp-deep .panel h4 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: 19px; color: #fff; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin: 10px 0 10px; }
    .tp-deep .panel p { font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.74); margin: 0; }

    /* Sample benchmark table (Business Growth only — scoped via .tp-bench) */
    .tp-bench { margin-top: 40px; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12); background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02); }
    .tp-bench .bench-head { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr 1fr 1fr; gap: 16px; padding: 14px 24px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.18); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--innovia-green); letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; }
    .tp-bench .bench-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr 1fr 1fr; gap: 16px; padding: 18px 24px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); align-items: baseline; }
    .tp-bench .bench-row:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
    .tp-bench .bench-row .kpi { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 600; font-size: 15px; color: #fff; }
    .tp-bench .bench-row .v { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 15px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78); }
    .tp-bench .bench-row .v.you { color: var(--innovia-green); font-weight: 700; }
    .tp-bench .bench-footnote { padding: 14px 24px; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.42); letter-spacing: 0.04em; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.10); }

    /* Rebate flow (Vendor Program only — scoped via .tp-flow) */
    .tp-flow { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 12px; margin-top: 40px; }
    .tp-flow .node { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12); padding: 20px; position: relative; }
    .tp-flow .node .ix-small { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; color: var(--innovia-green); letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; }
    .tp-flow .node h5 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: 16px; color: #fff; letter-spacing: -0.008em; margin: 8px 0 6px; }
    .tp-flow .node p { font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.66); margin: 0; }
    .tp-flow .node + .node::before { content: "→"; position: absolute; left: -16px; top: 50%; transform: translateY(-50%); font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--innovia-green); font-size: 16px; }

    .tp-faq { padding: 88px 0; background: var(--innovia-navy-deep); border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); }
    .tp-faq .head { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.6fr; gap: 64px; margin-bottom: 32px; align-items: start; }
    .tp-faq .head .ix { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--innovia-green); letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; }
    .tp-faq .head h2 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 800; font-size: clamp(28px, 3vw, 42px); color: #fff; letter-spacing: -0.02em; line-height: 1.05; margin: 14px 0 0; text-wrap: balance; }
    .tp-faq .head p { font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin: 14px 0 0; max-width: 56ch; }
    .tp-faq details { border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.14); padding: 24px 0; }
    .tp-faq details:last-of-type { border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.14); }
    .tp-faq details summary { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 600; font-size: 19px; color: #fff; letter-spacing: -0.008em; cursor: pointer; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; gap: 24px; list-style: none; }
    .tp-faq details summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
    .tp-faq details summary::after { content: "+"; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-weight: 400; color: var(--innovia-green); font-size: 24px; line-height: 1; flex: 0 0 auto; }
    .tp-faq details[open] summary::after { content: "−"; }
    .tp-faq details .a { font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.62; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.72); margin: 14px 0 0; max-width: 70ch; }
    .tp-faq details .a p { margin: 0 0 12px; }
    .tp-faq details .a p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

    .tp-cta { padding: 88px 0; background: var(--innovia-green); color: var(--innovia-navy); }
    .tp-cta .layout { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1.6fr 1fr; gap: 64px; align-items: center; }
    .tp-cta h2 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 900; font-size: clamp(32px, 4vw, 56px); color: var(--innovia-navy); letter-spacing: -0.026em; line-height: 1; margin: 0; text-wrap: balance; }
    .tp-cta p { font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.55; color: rgba(15,36,71,0.78); margin: 18px 0 0; max-width: 50ch; }
    .tp-cta .actions { display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
    .tp-cta .btn-primary { background: var(--innovia-navy); color: #fff; border: 0; padding: 14px 22px; font-family: var(--font-body); font-weight: 600; font-size: 15px; display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; text-decoration: none; transition: background .15s, transform .1s; }
    .tp-cta .btn-primary:hover { background: var(--innovia-navy-deep); }
    .tp-cta .btn-primary:active { transform: translateY(1px); }
    .tp-cta .btn-secondary { background: transparent; color: var(--innovia-navy); border: 1.5px solid var(--innovia-navy); padding: 12.5px 20px; font-family: var(--font-body); font-weight: 600; font-size: 15px; display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; text-decoration: none; transition: background .15s; }
    .tp-cta .btn-secondary:hover { background: rgba(15,36,71,0.08); }

    @media (max-width: 1080px) {
      .tp-pressure .layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 28px; }
      .tp-mechanic .steps { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
      .tp-mechanic .step:nth-child(2) { border-right: 0; padding-right: 0; }
      .tp-mechanic .step:nth-child(3) { border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12); padding-top: 28px; padding-left: 0; }
      .tp-mechanic .step:nth-child(4) { border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12); padding-top: 28px; }
      .tp-proof .strip { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 36px 0; }
      .tp-proof .stat:nth-child(2) { padding-right: 0; border-right: 0; }
      .tp-proof .stat:nth-child(3) { padding-left: 0; }
      .tp-deep .body { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 24px; }
      .tp-flow { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 24px; }
      .tp-flow .node + .node::before { display: none; }
      .tp-faq .head { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 14px; }
      .tp-cta .layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 32px; }
    }
    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .tp-mechanic .steps { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .tp-mechanic .step, .tp-mechanic .step + .step { border-right: 0; padding: 28px 0; }
      .tp-mechanic .step:first-child { padding-top: 0; }
      .tp-mechanic .step { border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12); }
      .tp-mechanic .step:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
      .tp-proof .strip { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .tp-proof .stat { border-right: 0; padding: 0 0 24px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12); }
      .tp-proof .stat:last-child { border-bottom: 0; padding-bottom: 0; }
      .tp-flow { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .tp-bench .bench-head, .tp-bench .bench-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 4px; padding: 12px 16px; }
      .tp-bench .bench-row .v::before { content: attr(data-label) " · "; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.4); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase; }
    }
  </style>



  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      
      <div class="crumb">
        <a href="/">Innovia</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <a href="/for-cams/why-innovia/">For CAMs</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <a href="/for-cams/three-pillars/">Three Pillars</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span style="color:#fff;">Vendor Program</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Vendor <em>program.</em><span class="light">Six pillars of pre-negotiated agreements. Industry-specific. Member-only.</span></h1>
      <p class="lede">The vendor program is the pillar that didn&rsquo;t need a rename. Members vote vendor partners onto the lineup, and partners defend the slot each year by member-rated performance. The cooperative never takes vendor money for placement.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pillar-detail">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="layout">
        <div class="col-left">
          <p class="num">03</p>
          <div class="legacy">Retained &middot; Vendor Program</div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-right">
          
          <div class="facet">
            <span class="ix">01</span>
            <div><h4>Banking &amp; Treasury</h4><p>Operating + reserve banking with CAM-fluent product teams, fee structures negotiated at cooperative scale, pass-through savings to your boards.</p></div>
          </div>
          <div class="facet">
            <span class="ix">02</span>
            <div><h4>Software &amp; AMS</h4><p>AMS, accounting, and integration partners audited at the member level. Member-rate licensing. Onboarding through the cooperative.</p></div>
          </div>
          <div class="facet">
            <span class="ix">03</span>
            <div><h4>AI &amp; Data Tooling</h4><p>AI tooling for the back office of community management. Vetted for security and accuracy before it lands in front of a manager.</p></div>
          </div>
          <div class="facet">
            <span class="ix">04</span>
            <div><h4>Staffing &amp; Talent</h4><p>Recruiting and contract staffing partners that understand the seats CAM companies actually need to fill.</p></div>
          </div>
          <div class="facet">
            <span class="ix">05</span>
            <div><h4>Insurance</h4><p>D&amp;O, GL, cyber, crime &mdash; carriers that price independent CAMs fairly because they understand the risk profile.</p></div>
          </div>
          <div class="facet">
            <span class="ix">06</span>
            <div><h4>Security &amp; Compliance</h4><p>Cybersecurity, payment security, and compliance partners that protect the data CAM companies hold.</p></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

<section class="tp-pressure">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="layout">
        <div>
          <span class="ix">No. 02 · The independent&rsquo;s penalty</span>
          <h2>Independents pay retail. Nationals pay wholesale.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="body">
          <p>A national CAM firm with five thousand communities walks into a banking RFP with leverage no regional firm can match alone. The same is true for insurance carriers, AMS vendors, AI tooling, payment processors, and the half-dozen other line items that quietly determine an independent&rsquo;s margin.</p>
          <p>The vendor program exists to close that gap. The cooperative aggregates member spend, negotiates terms on behalf of the room, and passes savings through. The vendor relationship is no longer one firm versus one supplier &mdash; it&rsquo;s a cooperative against a category.</p>
          <p class="pull">I had been overpaying our bank by 28 basis points for nine years.<cite>&mdash; A member, on their first cooperative banking review</cite></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="tp-mechanic">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="head">
        <span class="ix">How a vendor earns a seat</span>
        <h2>Proposed, vetted, negotiated, re-earned.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="steps">
        <div class="step">
          <span class="ix">Step 01</span>
          <h4>Proposed</h4>
          <p>Any member can nominate a vendor for the cooperative lineup &mdash; existing relationship, category they want covered, or category they want strengthened.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="ix">Step 02</span>
          <h4>Vetted</h4>
          <p>Reference checks across members, security and compliance review, financial stability check. Built specifically for CAM operations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="ix">Step 03</span>
          <h4>Negotiated</h4>
          <p>The cooperative negotiates pricing, rebate, and terms on aggregate member spend &mdash; not as a single-firm buyer.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="ix">Step 04</span>
          <h4>Re-earned</h4>
          <p>Every partner faces an annual member vote. Member-rated performance keeps a seat. Underperformance ends one.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="tp-proof">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="strip">
        <div class="stat"><span class="num">6</span><span class="label">Vendor categories covered</span></div>
        <div class="stat"><span class="num placeholder">$24&nbsp;M+</span><span class="label">Lifetime member savings &amp; rebates</span></div>
        <div class="stat"><span class="num">100%</span><span class="label">Member-rated, annually re-earned</span></div>
        <div class="stat"><span class="num">$0</span><span class="label">Vendor money for placement</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="tp-deep">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="head">
        <span class="ix">Governance</span>
        <h2>The cooperative never takes vendor money for placement.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="body">
        <div>
          <p>Most vendor programs in the industry are funded by the vendor &mdash; the &ldquo;preferred&rdquo; status is bought, not earned. The buyer never sees how that math works. The vendor never has to defend the seat.</p>
          <p><strong>The cooperative runs on the opposite model.</strong> Funding comes from members. Vendors compete for inclusion on terms, not on placement fees. The annual review is run by members, not by a sales team that needs the renewal.</p>
          <p>This is the boring, structural reason members trust the lineup. It&rsquo;s also the reason every rebate negotiated by the cooperative is passed through to the member &mdash; not kept as a placement margin.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="subhead" style="margin: 0 0 4px;">How rebates flow.</p>
          <p>Aggregate member spend earns negotiated terms with each preferred partner. The cooperative tracks volume and rebate accruals per member, and returns them on a quarterly cycle. Members see the math.</p>
          <div class="tp-flow">
            <div class="node"><span class="ix-small">01</span><h5>Aggregate spend</h5><p>Members direct vendor spend through cooperative agreements.</p></div>
            <div class="node"><span class="ix-small">02</span><h5>Negotiated terms</h5><p>Pricing and rebate negotiated on total member volume.</p></div>
            <div class="node"><span class="ix-small">03</span><h5>Tracked &amp; reported</h5><p>Cooperative tracks accruals; quarterly statements show the math.</p></div>
            <div class="node"><span class="ix-small">04</span><h5>Passed through</h5><p>Rebates flow back to the member firm &mdash; not the cooperative.</p></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="tp-faq">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="head">
        <div>
          <span class="ix">Common questions</span>
          <h2>Before you ask.</h2>
        </div>
        <p>The three questions every operator has about the vendor program. Direct answers; the longer conversation is a call away.</p>
      </div>
      <details>
        <summary>Do I have to switch all my existing vendors to join?</summary>
        <div class="a"><p>No. The cooperative is not an exclusivity contract. Members typically start by routing one or two categories through preferred partners &mdash; banking and AMS are the most common starting points &mdash; and evaluate from there. Existing vendor relationships can stay in place indefinitely.</p></div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How does the cooperative get paid?</summary>
        <div class="a placeholder">
          <p>[Client to confirm: membership fee structure. Working answer: the cooperative is funded by member dues, not by vendor placement fees or rebate skims. Rebates negotiated by the cooperative pass through to the member firm in full.]</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What happens if a preferred vendor underperforms?</summary>
        <div class="a"><p>Members rate each partner annually. Persistent underperformance &mdash; service issues, pricing creep, account-team turnover &mdash; can end a vendor&rsquo;s seat at the annual review. The seat is then opened to a member proposal cycle, which starts the four-step process from the top.</p></div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="tp-cta">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="layout">
        <div>
          <h2>Find out what your firm has been overpaying.</h2>
          <p>The first cooperative banking or insurance review pays for itself, in most cases, before the second category is touched.</p>
        </div>
